1
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:02,675
<b>For as long as philosophy
has asked its first question,</b>

2
01:00:02,850 --> 01:00:05,700
<b>existence has seemed
to call for explanation.</b>

3
01:00:06,708 --> 01:00:08,000
<b>Why is there anything at all?</b>

4
01:00:08,583 --> 01:00:10,916
<b>The mind reaches for a source,
a first cause,</b>

5
01:00:11,458 --> 01:00:13,875
<b>a final reason able to account
for the whole.</b>

6
01:00:14,958 --> 01:00:18,583
<b>There is awareness, a questioning process
in which the question appears.</b>

7
01:00:19,708 --> 01:00:22,666
<b>That occurrence belongs to the reality
we are trying to understand.</b>

8
01:00:23,916 --> 01:00:26,100
<b>This changes the meaning of "something."</b>

9
01:00:27,125 --> 01:00:31,458
<b>We usually think of something as a specific
object, event, or state of affairs.</b>

10
01:00:32,416 --> 01:00:34,000
<b>But in the deepest form of the question,</b>

11
01:00:34,500 --> 01:00:36,916
<b>something means the totality
of whatever exists.</b>

12
01:00:37,958 --> 01:00:40,500
<b>That totality includes the
questioner, the</b>

13
01:00:40,583 --> 01:00:43,083
<b>question, and any answer that
might be given.</b>

14
01:00:44,125 --> 01:00:47,666
<b>So every answer arises within the very
field it tries to explain.</b>

15
01:00:48,625 --> 01:00:52,375
<b>A complete explanation of everything would
have to include the explanation itself.</b>

16
01:00:53,583 --> 01:00:55,000
<b>It would have to include the act of</b>

17
01:00:55,083 --> 01:00:58,500
<b>understanding it, the system producing
it, and the conditions</b>

18
01:00:58,583 --> 01:01:00,166
<b>that make such production possible.</b>

19
01:01:01,500 --> 01:01:03,875
<b>Once the explanation exists, it becomes</b>

20
01:01:03,958 --> 01:01:06,208
<b>another part of what the explanation
must cover.</b>

21
01:01:07,125 --> 01:01:09,625
<b>The account is therefore drawn
into self-reference.</b>

22
01:01:10,833 --> 01:01:12,833
<b>To close over the whole,
it must include its</b>

23
01:01:12,916 --> 01:01:14,958
<b>own occurrence as one of the
things explained.</b>

24
01:01:16,125 --> 01:01:19,541
<b>Each attempt at final closure adds the
act of closure to the totality.</b>

25
01:01:20,708 --> 01:01:22,750
<b>This gives the deepest question
its boundary.</b>

26
01:01:23,500 --> 01:01:26,416
<b>The question can be asked, clarified,
and understood.</b>

27
01:01:27,250 --> 01:01:30,500
<b>It reveals that existence contains
the question of existence.</b>

28
01:01:31,875 --> 01:01:34,041
<b>We can ask why there is something
rather than</b>

29
01:01:34,125 --> 01:01:36,750
<b>nothing, because we are already
within the something.</b>

30
01:01:37,750 --> 01:01:40,000
<b>This is the precise shape of
the incompleteness.</b>

31
01:01:41,083 --> 01:01:42,958
<b>Existence can question itself
from within.</b>

32
01:01:43,666 --> 01:01:45,625
<b>It cannot close the case
from beyond itself.</b>

